<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The ZMH specimens correspond to a juvenile female and an adult male that clearly come from the type series. This species was transferred by 
<bibRefCitation author="Exline, H" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="577 - 620" title="Rhoicinine spiders (Pisauridae) of western South America." volume="29" year="1960">Exline (1960)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName class="Arachnida" family="Desidae" genus="Calacadia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Calacadia radulifera" order="Araneae" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radulifera">Calacadia radulifera</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Simon 1902</bibRefCitation>
). Exline presented a description of both male and female but it is difficult to determine which specimens she examined. She mentions on a foot note on page 168 that Dr. Levi examined the type in the MNHN but unfortunately no data are given and it is difficult to assess if these specimens were part of the type series. This species has never been illustrated before and we can only present the description of the male since the ZMH female specimen is a juvenile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
